      "raw_text": "The cavalcade went to the county\njail. where Sheriff Doust, after an\nexamination Of the property assigned\nto each man had been made and\nvouched for. accommodated the off,\nGERS with places for the prisoners.\nThirteen Of the men are charged\nwith selling liquor to Indians.\n\n\nThen Sam Senator. stood alone, but\n\n\nmodern degeneracy\" had touched\nhim. Sam Senator was a type of the\nYakima Indian-short and squatty in\nstature, with hat beaded and flutes\nat the edge of .the brim. He wore\nnone of the gorgeous blankets famil-\nlar to the Yakima visitors. He had\nstolen a horse belonging to Sid Sor-\nrow, a Yakima reservation Indian,\naccording to the charge."
    }
